node.text: I’m asking Ambassador Bill Burns to lead the Central Intelligence Agency because he’s dealt with many of the thorniest global challenges we face. As a legendary career diplomat, he approached complex issues with honesty, integrity and skill. That’s exactly how he’ll lead the CIA.

node.text:
We have no time to lose to address the economic crisis we face and build our economy back better.

This team will be ready on Day One to pull every lever of government to help those hardest hit by COVID-19 and right the structural inequalities in our economy.

node.text: Thanksgiving has always been a special time for the Biden family. And while I know this isn’t the way many of us hoped to spend the holiday, the small act of staying home is a gift to our fellow Americans.

node.text:
Today, I announced the first members of my national security and foreign policy team. They will rally the world to take on our challenges like no other—challenges that no one nation can face alone.

It’s time to restore American leadership. I trust this group to do just that.

node.text:
America, I’m honored that you have chosen me to lead our great country.

The work ahead of us will be hard, but I promise you this: I will be a President for all Americans — whether you voted for me or not.

I will keep the faith that you have placed in me.

buttons.text: Joe Biden is the President of the United States. Kamala Harris is the Vice President.

node.text: The “big lie” is just that—a big lie.

node.accessibility_caption: Joe Biden stands at a podium with his right hand pointing to the audience. A backdrop and plaque at the podium reads Build Back Better. Two American flags stand to his right.

node.text:
On this day last year during the economic crisis, we announced we weren’t just going back to the way things were—we were going to build back better. 

Our work continues strengthening the middle class, ensuring everyone is dealt-in, and building a more climate-resilient nation.

node.text: America is coming back—together.

Over 300 million shots administered.
Checks delivered to more than 169 million Americans.
More than three million jobs added to the U.S. economy.
 
We’ve come a long way. But this is just the beginning.

buttons.text: Visit the COVID-19 Information Center for vaccine resources.

node.accessibility_caption: Screenshot of Joe Biden tweet: Help us mark our independence from this virus—get vaccinated.

node.text: Get vaccinated.

buttons.text: Visit the COVID-19 Information Center for vaccine resources.

node.accessibility_caption: Joe Biden in a blue suit and tie stands at a podium. A sign behind him says vaccines.gov.

node.text:
The science is clear: The best way to protect yourself against the virus and its variants is to be fully vaccinated. 

If you have not been vaccinated, get your COVID-19 shot as soon as possible. Now is not the time to let our guard down.
